#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid ""
"Well, to be honest, I'm just a guy in cool suit…  I took it from museum when"
" <the_cataclysm> started to protect myself, and to somehow remain stable, I "
"started to think of myself as holy warrior, which was sent here to purge the"
" world of <zombies>…  Don't judge me, please…"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid ""
"Ok, ok, I'll play along.  But only if you start calling me 'The Chosen One'!"
" [*chuckles*]"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "HOW DARE YOU SAY SOMETHING LIKE THAT!!!"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Where is your cross, my brother?"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Where is your cross, my sister?"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Prove to be a true warrior of the light"
msgstr ""

#. ~ Description for mission '{'str': 'Prove to be a true warrior of the
#. light'}'
#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid ""
"Knight asked you to prove that you are true warrior of the light by killing "
"100 zombies."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid ""
"Look outside and tell me what you see there.  I see plague, plague upon "
"another plague that was sent to our world to purge it from its sins.  If you"
" want to help me fight this plague, and to clean this world from it, I want "
"you to prove me that you are true warrior of the light.  Kill 100 <zombies> "
"and return to me."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "I'll wait."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "What are you, infidel?!"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "God bless you!"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid ""
"It's good to see another warrior of the light.  I'm pleased to see that you "
"succeed in this task."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Um…"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Help Father Randalf"
msgstr ""

#. ~ Description for mission '{'str': 'Help Father Randalf'}'
#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Knight asked you to help Father Randolph to lift his curse."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid ""
"Ah, my fellow warrior of the light, it's good that you're alive.  I have "
"another task for you.  You need to help my dear brother, Brother Randolph, "
"to lift his curse, so that his soul could reach the heaven and rest "
"peacefully for eternity."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "I know you can do it! God bless you!"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Ah, what a relief!  You did good, my <name_g>."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Find relic"
msgstr ""

#. ~ Description for mission '{'str': 'Find relic'}'
#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid ""
"Knight asked you to find special relic, the remains of some priest that "
"lived in this land a few centuries ago."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid ""
"Ah, it's you again.  I have another task for you.  Did you know that this "
"church was built 287 years ago, and stood still to this day?  More "
"interesting, that this church was built by one man!  By one priest this "
"church was built, and he was called saint because of his will, pureness and "
"love for God.  Even more interesting, I learn from notes of current "
"(deceased, sadly) priest that his remains were kept in the basement, until "
"it was taken away by some research group to learn about its healing powers."
"  I want you to get back his remains."
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "I don't know what you will face there, but God will help you!"
msgstr ""

#: .\npc\Teachers\wanderer_knight.json
msgid "Ah, splendid!"
msgstr ""

